Thanks for your reply and +1 for Java APIs. 

The model file is said to be language agnostic, so I trained my model in Python and write a predict function in Java as below to deploy into the production environment.

``` Java
public void predict(NDArrayIter dataiter, int batchSize) {

    SGD opt = new SGD(0.0001f, 0.9f, 0.000f, 0.0f, null);
    Uniform uniform = new Uniform(0.1f);
    Context[] ctx = new Context[1];
    ctx[0] = Context.cpu(0);
    FeedForward model = FeedForward.load("prefix", 10, ctx, 200, 32, opt, uniform, 32, false);

    model.predict(dataiter, batchSize);
}
```

But I stuck at creating an NDArrayIter? I was going to start from creating an NDArray but failed at last. I found a quite similar issue here https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/issues/2583 ><

